The '''Best In The Desert''' (BITD) Racing Association is an American desert [[off-road racing]] association. It is operated by Casey Folks<ref name="offroad08212008">{{cite web|url=http://www.off-road.com/dirtsports/Desert+Racing:+BITD/BITD-Five-Minutes-with-Casey-Folks/ArticleStandard/Article/detail/543837?contextCategoryId=46499|title=BITD: Five Minutes with Casey Folks|last=Rousseau|first=Scott|date=August 21, 2008|publisher=Offroad.com|accessdate=2009-01-24}}</ref> and it is based out of [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]]. BITD runs the Vegas To Reno, the longest off-road race in the United States, and since 2012 is the sanctioning body of the [[Mint 400]].
